<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Seed" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Seed,</orth> that from wich plants spring: <bibl n="shak. ven 167" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.490" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 490</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 136</bibl> <emph>(an unweeded garden that grows to s.).</emph> Metaphorical use: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 93</bibl>. == offspring: <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 9, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 121</bibl>. == son, descendant: <cit><quote>saw his heroical s., and smiled to see him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 59</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to make them kings, the --s of Banquo kings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 70</bibl></cit> (M. Edd. <emph>seed</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>